The defendant Crystal M. Dankert was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court calls 15CM5, 15CM47, 15CM205 @ 1:28 pm. Defendant Crystal M. Dankert in court with attorney Alexander Paul Seifert.  Defendant Crystal M. Dankert in custody.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State received Revocation Packet and summary no corrections. Atty Seifert received revocation packet and summary and no corrections. Court heard on ct's that sentencing today is 15CM5 ct 1 15CM205 Ct 1 & 15CM47 Ct 1, 2, & 4.  State gives sentencing, credit15CM5 104 days, 205, 104 days, 47 96 days credit. State request Court to adopt DOC recommendation.  State gives defendant criminal history. State recommends, 6 months jail on each count.  Victim rights complied.  Victim makes statement.  Atty Seifert gives sentencing recommendation. Credit, 12 full days credit as trustee.  Def. makes statement.  Court questions on Restitution, State give statement.  Atty Seifert gives statement.  Court orders on 15CM5 Ct 1  170 days jail, 104 days credit, 15CM47 Ct 1 170 days jail,  96 days credit, Ct 2  170 days jail, Ct 4  170 days jail, 15CM205 Ct 1  170 days jail, 104 days credit.  All jail concurrent to each other. Court costs and restitution converted to civil judgment. Huber privileges. Def. advised of postconviction rights.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on December 7, 2017 at 01:30 pm.

records.addlTxt: Sentencing hearing on revocation on January 30, 2018 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Crystal M. Dankert in court with attorney Gary Stephen Dodge.  Jill Laufenberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CM5, 15CM205, and 15CM47 @ 1:50 p.m. Agreement stated - 15CM5 - Def will plead to charge, State has complied with VWNR, withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, counseling as deemed appropriate by agent, court costs, 10 days jail, huber, no contact with victim K.S. 15CM47 - Def will plead to cts 1, 2, & 4. Dismiss and read in cts 3 & 5. State has complied with VWNR. 1 yr probation, withheld sentence, AODA and treatment, court costs, $1450 restitution, joint & several. 15CM205 -Def will plead to charge, State has complied with VWNR, withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, $1500 restitution, no contact w/victim M.P., court costs, 10 days jail, huber, consecutive to 15CM5. State will not amend to add bail jumping charge. Atty Dodge and Def agree. Plea quest. reviewed. 15CM5 - no contest plea. 15CM47 ct 1 - no contest, ct 2 - no contest, ct 4 - no contest. 15CM205 - no contest plea. Court grants motion to dismiss cts 3 & 5 of 15CM47. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Dodge satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 15CM5 ct 1 misd battery, 15CM47 ct 1 receiving or concealing stolen property, ct 2 resisting/obstructing, ct 4 misd bail jumping, 15CM205 misd theft. Victim statement read by State. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Def requesting jail be served in Winnebago or Outagamie Co. Statement by Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court. 15CM5  withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, counseling deemed appropriate, court costs, no DNA sample/surcharge, no contact w/victim K.S., 7 days jail/huber. May be served in any county as long as no electronic monitoring. Must start 7 day sentence on or before 12/31/16. Credit for 1 day served. 15CM47 ct 1 - sentence withheld, 1 yr probation, AODA and follow through as ordered by agent, court costs, no DNA sample or surcharge on this count, $1450 restitution, joint & several with E.L. Def to report to probation in Langlade Co, may transfer to county resides in. ct 2 sentence withheld, 1 yr probation, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge. Ct 4 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, court costs, DNA surcharge, same conditions. All probation concurrent. 15CM205 ct 1 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, concurrent, restitution $1500 to M.P., court costs, DNA surcharge, 7 days jail, commence no later than 7/1/17, may serve in any county, huber, no electronic monitoring. Apply bond in 15CM5 to costs, any remaining apply to 15CM47. 15CM205 credit for 1 day served.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights.
